# __PLUGIN_PKG__

__DESCRIPTION__

A plugin for [KeepTrack.space](https://github.com/thkruz/keeptrack.space).

## Develop

The plugin needs the KeepTrack engine to compile against. Two common setups:

**A. Develop inside a KeepTrack checkout (recommended)**

```bash
git clone https://github.com/thkruz/keeptrack.space
cd keeptrack.space
npm install
npm run plugin -- create my-plugin      # scaffolds src/plugins-external/keeptrack-plugin-my-plugin
npm run plugin -- dev __CONFIG_KEY__    # boots the app with only this plugin, live-reload
```

Edit the files under `src/plugins-external/__PLUGIN_PKG__/`, then push them to
their own git repo (`git remote add origin …` from inside the plugin folder).

**B. Develop standalone**

Clone this repo next to a `keeptrack.space` checkout (so the `../keeptrack.space`
paths in `tsconfig.json` resolve), or clone KeepTrack into `.keeptrack-space/`.
Then `npm install` here for editor type-checking.

## Install (for users)

```bash
# From a KeepTrack checkout:
npm run plugin -- add https://github.com/YOU/__PLUGIN_PKG__
npm run build   # or restart `npm start`
```

## The two hard rules

1. The entry (`src/plugin.ts`) must have a **named export** matching `className`
   in `keeptrack-plugin.json` (`__CLASS_NAME__`).
2. The class's `readonly id` must **equal** its `configKey` (`__CONFIG_KEY__`).

